<font color="#FF0000">WHAT I KNOW ABOUT COMMUNIST</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jun 26 23:39:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To Tom:<br><br>
It was not a conventional war, but a &quot;people's war&quot;, as MAO (of china) defined it. It was a new kind of warfare opposed upon the people by the Communist in which there were no civilians. &quot;If you are not with us, you are against us---there is no third way to go.&quot; All the &quot;sacrifices&quot; --destruction and human losses, as far as the Communist concern-- are in-avoidable expenses and are sacred for one goal only: &quot;the final liberation of the whole human race.&quot; As the Communist believe, a lot of people must die and a great portion of the material world must be destroyed before the whole human race can step into the perfect world called Communism.<br><br>
You are probably right that it was a civil war and a lot of the Vietnam people supported the Communist North. But, it was also a part of that &quot;final liberation&quot; and the USA is the &quot;#1 public enemy&quot; in the Communist's eyes. As I mentioned  before, the Communist promised people everything, from land, job, welfare, to &quot;the ownership of the country&quot;. They showed people an easy way: to blame the rich, the system and foreign countries for our poverty and problems. Before we have tried that and ended up with economic and social chaos,---while the Party leaders have got everything the working-class dare not dream about--- this must have been pretty appealing to everyone, the peasants as well as to some of the educated-class seeking easy solutions. This must be the main reason why South Vietnam couldn’t survive while facing the challenge from the North.  <br><br>
Additionally, the Communist is indeed  terrorist groups. They don't reckon the value of human lives, which they regard as just screws or spare parts for the giant machine called Socialism Construction, and a dispensable element in the final battle for the liberation of the whole human race from evils like imperialism (e.g. the UK and France) and capitalism (i.e. the USA). They would invade people’s home, take everything they want, force family members to denounce their relatives who were on the other side---even a son to kill his landlord father in order to prove his stand, as a Chinese film depicted---, kill whoever they choose to kill as a warning to the public by declaring that person a public enemy or a landlord or a traitor or whatever and doing the execution publicly; they don't reckon civilians in this life-or-death battle! I don’t know what actually happened in Vietnam. Based on my knowledge of what the Chinese Communists had done in the Chinese civil war before, during, and after WWII, I can understand why &quot;a lot of the Vietnamese supported the Communist&quot;. My father was a Communist; his father, once a primary school principal, was a Communist, too. <br><br>
Usually, the governments facing a Communist takeover had some problems themselves; they might not be well democratic, they probably were corruptive at some extend. But, in the case of South Vietnam, they still had had public demonstrations, even  radical ones as monks immolating themselves, which is totally unthinkable under the Communist rule. There were no  public demonstrations possible in the communist world; few exceptions were all ended up in blood and bodies under tanks. And, I am almost sure that those monks left who were later liberated by the Communist probably haven’t survived the &quot;re-education&quot; camps. In China, the once damned Nationalists fled from mainland to Taiwain, where they are now building a democratic nation as well as perserving Chinese culture; while Beijing  has just announced that &quot;the current policy won’t  change for a hundred years&quot;. In Korea, the then government of the South was pretty much like the one you depicted in South Vietnam; the US and the United Nation gave it a chance by fighting the Communist North FOR IT, and have hence defended it; it held a free election years ago. If the South Vietnam government had had a chance, all those boat people might not have to risk their lives on the high seas; God knows how many of them have died out there. <br><br>
And, those of you who never witnessed the cruelty and the total ignorance for human life of the Communist probably will never fully understand why that young girl being burnt and was screaming and running naked in that famous photo is now taking asylum in Canada.<br><br>
You were fighting an un-winnable war in Vietnam against the Communist and their &quot;liberation of the whole human race from Imperialism and Capitalism&quot;. Your lost of that war was a tragedy for US, for Vietnam, for Southeast Asian as well as for the world. If America was strong enough then, probably the whole world would have adapted the American standard of human decency and human rights. But, anyway, at least from my point of view, you were not defending a corruptive South Vietnam government nor defending Imperialism, but defending America’s vision of a post-WWII world. And, indeed, it was the continuity of the war against Fascism in any means.<br><br>
BUT, EXCHANGING YOUNG AMERICAN LIVES (with all their dreams) FOR THOSE OF THE COMMUNISTS, WHO WOULD HAVE NO FUTURE ANYWAY, JUST DIDN'T WORTH IT! THIS PROBABLY IS THE MOST TRAGIC PART OF THAT WAR...<br><br>
America as the leader of the free world should has its vision of a post-coldwar world. As the wealthiest and freest nation on earth, USA has many enemies. The Communist in China is now the most dangerous one because they have atomic bombs and they don’t do body-counts. And they don’t believe there won’t be a winner in an atomic war, either. MAO once said that he would rather provoke the US to drop an atomic bomb in China killing a million people so as it would  disgrace itself in front of the whole world. The leaders now are not so maniac but they are still capable of doing a lot of evil. The discussion of  whether the Most Favored  or a sanction is the best way for China’s democracy is false because the Communist have been destroying the souls of the Chinese people and are destroying more and more souls of the children each day. By compromising on MFN and many other issues like human rights and forced abortion, USA is not only denouncing its own value but also helping Beijing kill souls.  And it is dangerous for US itself as well, because the profit the Communist get from the MFN will greatly reinforce their power, politically and militarily. Soon the USA would have to fight another cold-war. And this time, there would be 1.2 BILLION people on the other side.<br><br>
Thank you all for having defended American vision and American value.  --- Tao
